      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/663e46e98aef8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/663a72806b8df.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/663a72812417d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/663a728128f48.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/663a72814e2e9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/663a728127b90.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/663a72814ab8e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Peach &amp; Daisy Upgrade&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Peach and Daisy's jump power has been increased from -10% to -5%.&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Modified "README.txt" file to reflect the above change.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;Are you getting bored of playing as Mario every single time? Do you want to play Super Luigi U, but in Super Mario Wonder? Do you want your character to affect the way you play the game? &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;(if you answered yes to any of these questions, this mod is for you!)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod changes the game by allowing the character selected by Player 1 to influence the physics for all players, creating a fresh and unique gameplay experience.&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt; Luigi can jump higher but is harder to control.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Princess Peach can float, and Princess Daisy can spin jump, although both are slow and have a lower jump.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Blue Toad and Yellow Toad are both fast, but have a lower jump, with Yellow Toad maintaining physics that are more similar to Mario.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;Toadette has Mario's physics, but they are slightly different and better, making her the "Easy Mode" character just like in Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;If you want to know, in detail, how the physics look like, press &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WPuGwfrYcrc" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;b&gt;here&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;a href="//null"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
